We said earlier that any stream operation must be preceded by the open() function invocation. There are three well-defined exceptions to the rule.

When our program starts, the three streams are already opened and don't require any extra preparations. What's more, your program can use these 
streams explicitly if you take care to import the sys module:


import sys
 
Let's analyze them:

sys.stdinStandard InputLeer datos que entran
sys.stdoutStandard OutputMostrar datos normales
sys.stderrStandard ErrorMostrar errores

import sys

# Redirigimos stderr al archivo
sys.stderr = open("errores.log", "w")

sys.stderr.write("Este error ya no aparece en pantalla\\n")
sys.stderr.write("Se guarda directo en errores.log\\n")

